comments.commentBody: I'd like to see them go after Leonard Lance (R, NJ) for printing and mailing at least three expensive, glossy blatantly campaign pieces at taxpayers' expense. In all my 70 years I've never received mail like this ... from anyone. Oh, and in these mailers, he tells how he's working hard to reduce and eliminate government waste. Hypocrite! I can hardly wait to vote against him.
Who needs TV?

I was born in 79....but having studied the tax structure then and now coupled with the economic figures...You would think everyone in Ohio would vote democrat just to kill the idea of a tax break for the top 2%.  Pre Reagan their tax rate was around 70% even if it goes back to the pre-bush level it is still way lower than its been in the past, and yet they just keep expanding and expanding their holdings while suppressing wage increases and exporting jobs.

With October just around the corner, the tide will soon be turning back to the Democrats.  The Tea Party people have been hyped up too much on caffeine load. Reality will soon return...with goals and progress incentives, the people of Connecticutt and the rest of the U.S. will soon see that the season of the witch, and of the wrestling queen and others, is over.  Back to the road toward happy days again.  Let's fix America's problems and not turn back to what created them.

In some cases, unfortunately, one has to choose the greater of two lesser candidates! I for one would choose the one who lied about his service record, not least because he has a record of achievement in public service. McMahon has no record of service, except to herself; her accomplishments came on the back of her employees and relate not a wit to the challenges of helping us out of our mess; and she espouses nothing more than 'money can buy you an election' (an unfortunate truth in so many cases) and W-era platitudes... Save me from politicians, save me especially from McMahon. Tweedle-D is far better than Tweedle-dumb.
They helped keep Bush in place for a second term allowing him to complete the disaster that he almost confessed to two years ago today.  It's self-loathing projected as anger at any available target.

With democrats like these, who needs Republicans?  What is so awful about taxing return on capital and return on labor at the same rate?  And how many of these "democrats" so worried about senior citizens would willingly sign onto Republican plans to destroy Social Security?  Probably most.  Apparently the plutocrats are going all in these days to keep us peasants in our place.

Wow!  The Democrats protect some of their most unethical members and then threaten the Republicans who complain about it.  This nation is starting to be in a very scary place.  Democrats seem like they want to loot and harm the nation and then threaten the people who are most anxious to protect us.  My wife has been looking for a new job since March 2009.  What do the Democrats do?  They protect the cheaters and liars and bring in comedians to distract us from our pain.

#2 - mike

My wife has been looking for a new job since March 2009. She never faced this sort of difficulty when Bush was President. We are being hammered by a failed stimulus package which has clearly made things worse...not better. My stocks are up today. I would greatly prefer being able to invest the money taken from me - without my permission - for social security.

Can someone give me 3 speeches Obama did that were not attacking some party or organization, vilifying an industry, or blaming something on someone else?

I am looking for something where he was presidential.

E. Nowak #9, Not to nitpick, but I think President Obama has been governing exactly as he promised before he was elected.  He is a moderate Democrat, and tries to bring all sides to the table.  I agree that it hasn't worked all of the time, but that is who the man is.  And face it, he has been a tad busy.  I think he expected the House and the Senate to step up and take care of business themselves.  The House has done a very admirable job, it's the Senate where everything seems to fall apart, due to their crazy rules, such as Jim DaMint threatening to shut down the government all by his lonesome.

Nacho guy, why not get the real facts instead of some left winger spouting off? ND's population has increased, though not by a great deal since 2000. Don't take my word for it, take the word of the Census Bureau.
http://quickfacts.census.gov...
Dang inconvenient facts again. As far as federal spending per capita, it isn't subsidies. Instead it may have something to do with the fact that there are two major air bases in ND, which will skew federal per capita spending because of ND's low overall population. Also, since ND has a longer life expectancy, the amount of SS paid out is also higher per capita. I know it's hard to understand all this, but do try.
Adam, check out the same link. It shows ND, which is a pretty solid red state, has a lower than national average poverty rate. It also has a much lower crime rate than, say, Ann Arbor, where Nacho is from.

Shoot.  I'm cheap.  Whitman could have easily bought my vote by giving only $118 million dollars of the $119 million she spent on this election to help our State's schools, our incredible parks, the uninsured, the poor and our vets!  We gotta give Brown a chance to make California Golden again.  Step up and vote, it is your only voice for change.

I think the fact that 26,500 turned out in Wisconsin is very hopeful that the Democrats can turn this around by election day.  It's all about turnout.  The President's speech was great.  He's right. This is not the time to lose heart and quite by staying home.  People should not allow their disappointment in what has been done or not done to keep them home on election day.  Don't do it for the President or the party.  Vote in your own self interest!  The Republican tea party have vowed to undo everything that has been accomplished in the last two years.  They are extremists of the worst order.  Get out there....vote and work to turn out the voters.  Do it for yourself and everyone else.

I have to admit that I voted and supported Pres Obama after the primary, but now it is obvious that his lack of experience and Wash DC knowhow  has greatly reduced  his ability to lead us effectively.   As a democrat I believe it is time to accept that this presidency should be a one term affair and that we should give Hilary her shot at leadership of the party and the country because it certainly looks like the republicans are not going to find any leadership in their party for some time to come... Lets get out of this war in Afghanistan that is obvious we can not win or if we did win, so what  !!,,, what a colossal waste of our armed forces and our wealth.  Time for Hilary and her army to begin building another election bid campaign, the time for our first woman president is here....

He came to his religion because it was expedient to have a faith to hold public office. The precepts he holds can just as easily be construed in the context of the way he was raised by his birkenstock mom and radical lefitst father. Once a "one-worlder" always one. Is it November, 2012 yet? We want our country back.
I lived in Ohio for a time in the early 70's, that was enough to make me angry.

Support for Republicans doesn't make sense.

The Democrats had a mandate representing the majority of Americans. The Republicans did everything they could to block the will of the majority of Americans. What value system does this represent? Certainly not democracy.

And now Americans to return Republicans to power because they allowed so little to be accomplished?

Get rid of the people who prevented the will of the majority of Americans from being carried out and watered down the solutions. That means clear out the Republicans, who voted en masse--even against things they suggested! Do not reward them.

Jerry Brown was a wonderful mayor of Oakland and as the state attorney general, he prosecuted those local officials who were giving themselves astronomical salaries in Bell city. As governor of Ca he saved the public beaches in Lake Tahoe from being swallowed up by building prospectors and, he certainly knows how to lead.

Jack writes: "No U.S. president has spoken with such strength and conviction his dedication for the average American worker."

Talk is great but you need to walk the walk! Could you please explain how policies like a job-killing cap and trade law, ObamaCare and other assorted regulations are helping the working individual? It is certainly not creating private sector jobs - indeed, quite the opposite! Unemployment is now almost 2% higher than when he took office. And, the national debt will mean working class folks will have to pay more and more in taxes down the road.

If Obama truly care about the working folks, he'd unleash their collective abilities by getting off the backs of the job creators in the private sector!

please, other 49, force us to secede.
we'd be better off on our own.
The Dems are going to get crushed her on this issue. The have to vote to extend the cuts for ALL taxpayers, or else they will lose more than they expect.
I wonder why we do not hear, nor does the press mention or speak to Obama's sister Maya.

I couldn't care less about our president's choice of iPod music or his favorite  after shave, but what he has to say about Fox News is 100% accurate!  That channel, with its right wing nut hate mongers appeals to the ignorant, and because this type of coverage appeals to the less enlightened -- who are schmoozed into thinking it is accurate -- it is very destructive, maybe unconstitutional, as an attempt to divide the country through false reporting.
It's the people who go to church every week that I trust the least and from my findings to be the biggest hypocrites and who judge the most!
